<DIV align=center><B>&raquo;</B></DIV></TD>
<TD><A href="#story9">Upcoming Deadlines </A></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></P></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE><SPAN class=subhead><BR><A name=story1></A>2008 www.CESweb.org Re-launch</SPAN> <BR>The official website for the 2008 International Consumer Electronics Show has opened its cyber doors. CESweb.org is your one-stop source for information pertaining to the 2008 International CES, including; all contact information, exhibitor lists, press lists, award deadlines, speaker information and more. Make sure to bookmark <A href="http://www.cesweb.org/">www.CESweb.org/</A> and use the site often as a reference when planning for the 2008 show.<BR><BR><SPAN class=subhead><A name=story2></A>Exhibitor PR Manual Available</SPAN><U><STRONG><BR></U></STRONG>Jumpstart your 2008 public and investor relations campaigns and download the 2008 Exhibitor PR Manual to take full advantage of the 4,500 media and 2,200 financial/market analysts who attend the International CES. Learn how to generate pre-show publicity, schedule an on-site press conference, compile an eye-catching press kit and prepare targeted information for the financial community. You'll also find key CES contact information, a list of important deadlines and many ideas on how to make sure the 2008 International CES is a success for your company. It is a must-have for any PR/IR professional involved in the show. The 2008 PR Manual is now available online at <A href="http://www.cesweb.org/Exhibitors/PR">www.CESweb.org/Exhibitors/PR</A>.<BR><BR><SPAN class=subhead><A name=story3></A>PR Contact Information Requirement</SPAN><U><STRONG><BR></U></STRONG>The 2008 International CES is about more than your booth. It is a chance to brand your company name and maximize your opportunities before, during and after the show. To assist your public relations staff with your CES investment, we send information throughout the year about promotional opportunities as part of your CES Exhibitor Package. <BR><BR>The contacts you list will be individuals to whom we will direct any inquiries we receive regarding your company or products. The contact information will also be posted on CESweb.org for access by the media and other visitors to the CES website.&nbsp; <STRONG>It is required </STRONG>that you&nbsp;<A href="http://www.cesweb.org/exhibitors/resource_center/directory/default.asp">add/update your Exhibitor PR Contact information</A>.<BR><BR><SPAN class=subhead><A name=story4></A>2008 CES Registration Information</SPAN><BR>Online registration for the 2008 International CES is now open! Visit <A title=www.CESweb.org href="http://www.cesweb.org/Register">www.CESweb.org/Register</A> to register for CES and experience the hottest products, people and trends in the industry!<BR><BR><SPAN class=subhead><A name=story5></A>CES Unveiled</SPAN><U><STRONG><BR></U>CES Unveiled@NY<BR></STRONG>Tuesday, November 13, 2007<BR>Metropolitan Pavilion<BR>New York, NY<BR><BR>Jumpstart your CES success early at the annual New York CES Press Preview featuring Unveiled@NY - a kick off to the 2008 International CES promotion season. Debut your company's new products to more than 300 trade and consumer media, as well as market and financial analysts, at the CES Unveiled tabletop event. Don't miss your chance to stand out in the crowd and network with the hottest media in the key weeks leading up to the 2008 International CES.<BR><BR>Tabletop exhibitors at CES Unveiled@NY receive: 
<P></P>
<UL type=disc>
<LI>Demonstration and networking opportunities </LI>
<LI>Pre-event promotion of all event exhibitors and sponsors to CES' worldwide media list </LI>
<LI>One hundred fifty (150) word product description in the <EM>CES Unveiled Program Guide</EM>, subject to print deadline </LI>
<LI>One (1) six-foot draped exhibit table </LI>
<LI>Six (6) exhibitor passes to the event </LI>
<LI>One (1) 22' x 26" pole sign </LI>
<LI>500 watts of electrical service </LI>
<LI>Free high-speed Internet service </LI>
<LI>Use of the contact list of press who pre-registered for the Event and the list of press who attend the Event</LI></UL>
<P><STRONG>CES Unveiled: The Official Press Event of the International CES <BR></STRONG>Saturday, January 5, 2008<BR>Sands Expo and Convention Center/The Venetian<BR>Las Vegas, NV<BR><STRONG><BR></STRONG>Grab the media's attention two days before the world's largest consumer technology tradeshow even starts. CES Unveiled gives tabletop exhibitors the exclusive opportunity to display their hot new products to more than 800 media and analysts from around the world, including more than 130 international media from 30 countries, two days before the show opens! Media look to CES Unveiled exhibitors to preview what will be the hot and exciting products at the 2008 International CES.<BR><BR>Tabletop exhibitors at CES Unveiled in Las Vegas receive: </P>
<UL>
<LI>Demonstration and networking opportunities </LI>
<LI>Pre-event promotion of all Event exhibitors and sponsors to CES' worldwide media list </LI>
<LI>One hundred fifty (150) word product description in the <EM>CES Unveiled Program Guide</EM>, subject to print deadline </LI>
<LI>The opportunity to exhibit with the Best of Innovations Design and Engineering Showcase honorees </LI>
<LI>One (1) six-foot draped exhibit table </LI>
<LI>Six (6) exhibitor passes to the Event </LI>
<LI>One (1) 22' x 26" pole sign </LI>
<LI>500 watts of electrical service </LI>
<LI>Free high-speed Internet service </LI>
<LI>Use of the contact list of press who pre-registered for the Event and the list of press who attend the Event</LI></UL>
<P>For more information on Unveiled@NY and/or CES Unveiled in Las Vegas, including tabletop and sponsorship opportunities, package pricing and discounts for Innovations honorees, please contact Ryan Strowger at (703) 907-7679, or <U><A href="mailto:CESUnveiled@CE.org">CESUnveiled@CE.org</A></U>. For more information, visit <A title=www.cesweb.org/PressEvents href="http://www.cesweb.org/PressEvents">www.CESweb.org/PressEvents</A>.<BR><BR><SPAN class=subhead><A name=story6></A>Speaker Submissions (July 13 deadline)</SPAN><U><STRONG><BR></U></STRONG>The 2008 International CES Call for Speakers is now open! You may secure a speaking opportunity for you, your company or your client by answering the 2008 International CES Call for Speakers, now through <STRONG>Friday, July 13, 2007.<BR><BR></STRONG>More than 140,000 industry professionals from 140 countries will come to Las Vegas to see cutting-edge technology at the 2008 International CES, featuring four days of conference sessions, keynote speeches and exhibits of consumer technology.&nbsp; A speaking position in the CES conference program is your opportunity to reach the financial analysts, venture capitalists, developers, consumer technology manufacturers, corporate buyers and retailers that come to the show.<BR><BR>The 2008 International CES will host conference sessions addressing wireless technology, home networking, in-vehicle technology, emerging technologies, retailing trends, e-commerce, digital content and much more.&nbsp; Please see the Call for Speakers online entry form for a full list of conference subjects.<BR><BR>To be considered for a speaking opportunity at the 2008 International CES, <A href="http://www.cesweb.org/attendees/conferences/speakers/rd_speaker_form.asp">complete the online submission form</A>.<BR><BR>All submissions should include a 75 to 100 word biography, a photo and at least three key points that you can address for each session you selected.&nbsp; Should you be chosen to speak at the 2008 International CES, your bio and photo will be posted on <A title=www.cesweb.org href="http://www.cesweb.org/">www.CESweb.org/</A>.<BR><BR>All entrants will be contacted on or before September 28, 2007 as to their acceptance to the 2008 International CES conference program. For questions, please contact <A href="mailto:cfs@ce.org"><STRONG>CFS@CE.org</STRONG> </A>or <STRONG>(703) 907-7672</STRONG>.&nbsp;<BR><BR><SPAN class=subhead><A name=story7></A>Sponsorship Opportunities</SPAN><U><STRONG><BR><BR></U></STRONG><STRONG>VIP Buyers Car Service &amp; Luncheon</STRONG><BR>The VIP Buyers Sponsorship includes the <STRONG>VIP Buyer Car Service</STRONG> and <STRONG>VIP Luncheon</STRONG>.&nbsp; Make your company name and logo visible to a select group of presidents, owners, CEOs, merchandisers and buyers from the top 150 consumer electronics retail companies.<BR><BR><STRONG>E-mail Campaign</STRONG><BR>Coordinate your e-marketing campaign with the extensive International CES marketing campaign.&nbsp; Add your message to CES e-mails and reach more than 80,000 readers per e-mail, including pre-registrants and 2007 International CES attendees, loyal CES customers, conference attendees, VIP buyers, an international audience and more.<BR><BR><STRONG>Email Stations</STRONG><BR>Attendees rely on e-mail to keep in touch with daily business.&nbsp; Sponsors promote their company name, graphics and home page at e-mail stations in the busy, easy-access lobbies of International CES venues. <BR><BR><STRONG>Sponsorship Benefits</STRONG> </P>
<UL type=disc>
<LI>Twenty (20) e-mail stations, located in the LVCC Grand Lobby and South Lobby. </LI>
<LI>Sponsor signage </LI>
<LI>Directional signage leading to the e-mail stations from all venues. </LI>
<LI>Sponsor's website or CES booth message as the home page. </LI></UL>
<P>For questions regarding CES sponsorship opportunities, please contact <STRONG>Wendy Hudak</STRONG> at <A href="mailto:whudak@CE.org">whudak@CE.org</A> or <STRONG>(678) 457-4867.</STRONG> <BR><BR><SPAN class=subhead><A name=story8></A>2008 CES Hotel Information</SPAN><U><STRONG><BR></U></STRONG>Book your hotel reservations online at <A href="http://www.cesweb.org/Hotel">www.CESweb.org/Hotel</A> today! Oftentimes exhibitors need to reserve a block of rooms, so we have a block room request online that connects you directly with the hotels in Las Vegas that offer CES discounts. We also post the CES room rates, which fluctuate depending on availability, so if you can check this off your "to-do" list early, you'll likely save money.<BR><BR><SPAN class=subhead><A name=story9></A>Upcoming Deadlines</SPAN></P>
